review_text: Very relaxing park. Lots of chairs you can lounge. Very family oriented. Great place to work out. And just relax

There's also a public bathroom behind the stage.
In winter times, there's an ice rink on the open field

Obviously, it is more appealing with a temperature that allows humans to be there at least one hour without problems, but nature has its beauty all the time. You can walk, take a sunbath or play pétanque! People from "Université de Montréal" and the HEC, use to come at lunch time. Nice place!

- covered dance floor made of concrete
- lounging area with chairs
- kids playgrounds (3)
